[SN]TITLE[SN]
Qatar Ladies Open: Wales's Lydia Hall finishes joint-second

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Wales's Lydia Hall shot a final three-under-par round of 69 to finish joint-second at the Qatar Ladies Open.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 28-year-old had shared the halfway lead but a disappointing third round of 72 saw her slip down the leaderboard.
She rallied on the final day to share second, on 12 under, with Sweden's Caroline Hedwall, three behind 18-year-old winner Aditi Ashok of India.
